-- Oil surges to new record highs
-- 
-- Mon Oct 15, 2007 6:16am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/15/us-brent-crude-record-idUSWLA135020071015

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - London Brent and U.S. crude oil futures rose more than $1 to hit new record highs on Monday, as tension rose between Turkey and Iraq. 

 Brent was up $1.25 at $81.80 by 8:06 a.m. EDT, off highs of $81.93, while U.S. crude was $1.17 up at $84.88, off highs of $85.19.